description:
Bomb on Board

Aired on 10/12/2005, Narrated by: Jonathan Aris.

On 11 December 1994, Philippine Airlines Flight 434, a Boeing 747-200B, had a bomb explode on the second leg of a service flight from Manila to Tokyo via Cebu City. The explosion killed a passenger, injured many others and damaged some of the aircraft's control systems. The crew successfully land the aircraft at Naha Airport in Okinawa.
